				<p>I'm not sure what you're intending, but **do not use the chassis as a substitute for wired grounds**.  This goes double for an aluminum chassis, because aluminum can (and will eventually) oxidize, causing your connections to arc, fail, or both.  Set up a common ground in your circuitry, then connect that common ground to the chassis.</p>
